### [Falcon Perception](https://huggingface.co/blog/tiiuae/falcon-perception) — Hugging Face Blog  
Falcon Perception is a 0.6‑B transformer that fuses image patches and language prompts, outputting instance masks, coordinates, and size tokens via a single back‑bone. Hybrid attention lets image tokens attend bidirectionally while text tokens attend causally, allowing a shared encoder–decoder architecture. On SA‑Co, it achieves 68.0 % macro‑F1, beating SAM 3, and the lightweight design cuts GPU usage by ~3× on an A100 when served with vLLM.

### [Granite 4.0 3B Vision](https://huggingface.co/blog/ibm-granite/granite-4-vision) — Hugging Face Blog  
